the center with the pawn break ...[c5] and try to find counterplay on the queenside. White will try to build up an attack on the kingside thanks to their advanced [e5]-pawn.} c5 {Black immediately starts counterattacking the center.} 4. c3 {We reinforce our center.} Qb6 {[%csl Rc8][%cal Yc8d7,Yd7b5] Black delays the development of the [b8]-knight. This move is usually played first to solve the French bishop issue with a quick ...[Bd7]-[b5].} 5. Nf3 {We continue our development and are waiting for Black to show their cards.} Bd7 {[%csl Rd7,Gf1][%cal Rd7b5]} (5... Nc6 {would transpose into our mainline. As mentioned previously, Black's idea is to solve the problem of the French bishop as quickly as possible.}) 6. Na3 $5 {[%cal Rd7b5,Ga3b5] It is also possible to go on [a3] with our good friend here. It also has the benefit of preventing the ...[Bb5]-idea. For instance, the game could continue:} cxd4 {[%cal Rf8a3] The logical follow-up. Black wants to take advantage of what they see as a 'misplaced' knight. Other moves will transpose to lines we already explored via a different move order.} 7. cxd4 Bxa3 {[%csl Gc1] Black takes on [a3] to damage our pawn structure. However, the drawback is that this capture concedes White all the dark squares and opens the b-file for the [a1]-rook.} 8. bxa3 {[%csl Gc1][%cal Ba1b1,Gf1d3]} Ne7 (8... Nc6 {would transpose to previous lines.}) 9. Bd3 {[%cal Ga1b1,Ge1g1] We continue our development by putting the bishop on his best diagonal. At the same time, this move helps to prepare both [O-O] and [Rb1].} Nbc6 {[%csl Rd4] The most common move. Black wants to put pressure on the [d4]-pawn.} 10. Rb1 {We defend our pawn indirectly by attacking the Black's queen.} Qa5+ {It is possible to meet this check by putting the bishop or the queen on [d2]. But I'll recommend what I consider the best:} 11. Kf1 {[%csl Rb7][%cal Gh2h4,Gb1b7,Bg2g3,Bf1g1,Bg1g2,Yh1h3,Yh3g3] And White has the upper hand. We can continue with [Rxb7] or [h4] and our typical ideas next. Our king will be safe either on [g1] or [g2].} *

