[GameId "2180482215479403"]

11. b4 $1 {[%cal Ga2a4,Rc6a5,Gf1d3] This move simultaneously defends the [b2]-pawn and claims space on the queenside. White already holds a comfortable advantage.} *

[Event "Dynamite 1.e4: Advance French for White"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Key Middlegame Themes & Plans"]
[Black "Kingside Space - g4 Idea"]
[Result "1-0"]
[ECO "C02"]
[PlyCount "67"]
[GameId "2180482215491692"]

1. e4 {This is a Blitz game I played. We will see another common pawn push we should always have in mind.} e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qb6 6. Na3 Bd7 7. Nc2 Nge7 8. Bd3 Nf5 9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. O-O O-O {This is the instructive position. How to continue?} 11. g4 $1 {We are not afraid of weakening the protection of our king as Black can't take advantage of our move.} Nh6 12. Bxh6 {Now it is time to damage Black's pawn structure.} gxh6 13. Qd2 {[%csl Rh6] I put pressure on the [h6]-pawn and force Black's next move:} Kg7 {And now comes:} 14. g5 $1 Rg8 (14... Be7 15. gxh6+ Kh8 16. Kh1 {With similar ideas as in the game.}) (14... h5 15. Qf4 {We will continue with [Qh4]-[Qxh5] next.}) 15. gxh6+ Kh8+ 16. Kh1 {[%cal Gf1g1,Gd2f4] And we have ideas such as [Rg1], [Qf4], etc. Black's position will collapse soon.} Rg6 {Black panicked in the game and made things simple.} 17. Bxg6 fxg6 18. b4 Be7 19. a4 Rf8 20. a5 Qc7 21. Qe3 Rf5 22. Ncd4 Rxe5 23. Nxe5 Qxe5 24. Nxc6 Qxe3 25. fxe3 Bxc6 26. Rf7 Bd6 27. Raf1 {Bringing the last rook into the game.} Kg8 28. Rg7+ Kh8 29. Rff7 d4+ 30. Kg1 dxc3 31. Rxh7+ Kg8 32. Rhg7+ Kh8 33. h7 c2 34. Rg8# {And Black resigns.} 1-0

[Event "Dynamite 1.e4: Advance French for White"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Key Middlegame Themes & Plans"]
[Black "Pushing the h-Pawn to h6"]
[Result "1-0"]
[ECO "C02"]
[PlyCount "61"]
[GameId "2180482215508077"]

{Here is another of my Blitz games. We will see how we can push the h-pawn forward to create weaknesses into Black's camp.} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 cxd4 5. cxd4 Nc6 6. Nf3 Nge7 7. Na3 a6 8. Nc2 Ng6 {The knight is misplaced on [g6] and invites our next move:} 9. h4 {[%cal Gh4h5] It is difficult not to be tempted! We are ready to continue with [h5] to harass Black's knight followed by [h6] to create more weaknesses into Black's position.} Be7 (9... h5 10. Bd3 {White will take advantage of the [g5]-square easily while Black can't do the same about the [g4]-square.}) 10. h5 Nf8 11. h6 {With this move, we want to damage Black's pawn structure and create weaknesses on the dark squares in their position.} g6 {[%csl Rh7,Rg7,Rf6] Black has weaknesses on the dark squares. At the same time, the [h7]-pawn is fixed and will be a long-term weakness in the endgame.} (11... gxh6 12. Bd3 {There is no hurry to recapture the pawn. Black is positionally busted.}) 12. Bd3 Nd7 13. Bd2 Qb6 14. Rb1 (14. b4 {was also playable.}) 14... Nb4 15. Nxb4 Bxb4 16. a3 Bxd2+ 17. Qxd2 {[%csl Rh6,Rh7] Exchanging pieces will not help Black as we still have enough pieces to take advantage of their weaknesses.} Qd8 18. b4 {Grabbing space on the queenside.} b5 19. Rc1 {Taking control over the c-file. I want to play on both sides of the board.} Bb7 20. Ke2 {The king is safe in the center as the position is closed.} O-O 21. Qf4 {[%cal Gc1c3,Gh1c1,Bf4f6,Bf6g7,Bf3h2,Bh2g4,Bg4f6] The plan is to double rooks on the c-file while keeping in mind ideas such as Qf4-[f6]-[g7]# and [Nh2]-[g4]-[f6] to take advantage of the dark-square weaknesses.} f5 22. exf6 Rxf6 23. Qc7 {I decided to switch to an endgame where my rooks on the 7th rank will make the difference.} Rb8 24. Qxd8+ Rxd8 25. Rc7 Bc8 26. Rhc1 {All of the black pieces are passive.} Rff8 27. Ne5 Nxe5 28. Rg7+ {[%cal Gc1c7] Taking advantage of the [h6]-pawn!} Kh8 29. dxe5 {[%cal Gc1c7]} Rd7 30. Rxc8 Rxc8 31. Rxd7 {Black resigns.} 1-0

