[Black "Benko Compensation"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "r1b1k2r/pp2npp1/1qn1p2p/3pP3/3P4/3B1N2/P1NQ1PPP/R4RK1 w kq - 0 13"]
[PlyCount "3"]
[GameId "2180482215544943"]

{This is a typical position for our variation. White is down a pawn but has compensation thanks to their lead in development. This is quite similar to the 'Benko', except the engine also likes our position here!} 13. Rab1 {[%cal Gf1c1] Our rooks will come on the b- and c-files and put pressure against Black's position.} Qc7 14. Rfc1 {[%csl Gb1,Gc1][%cal Gc2e3] The rooks put pressure on the c-file. In the future, we can double rooks on the b- or c-files. It is also possible to lift the rook on the kingside if needed for an attack. Our next move in such positions will be [Ne3] when we will go for one of the knight maneuvers we mentioned earlier in this chapter.} *

