the scores even more!} cxd4 {Black's main choice by far.} 7. cxd4 {The main tabiya.} Bb4+ 8. Bd2 Bxa3 $6 {The second most common continuation in games of amateurs. I consider this move dangerous as it surrenders to White the control over all the dark squares.} 9. bxa3 {[%cal Ga1b1] Black has to accept the challenge and capture our [d4]-pawn as we are threatening to continue with [Rb1] next.} Nxd4 {The right continuation. White's score in this position is excellent after our next move:} 10. Qa4+ Nc6 11. Bd3 {[%csl Rg7,Gd3,Gd2][%cal Ge1g1,Ga1b1,Ga4g4] We continue with our developement. We are ready to continue with [O-O], [Rb1], [Rfc1], [Qg4], etc. Black's position is already difficult to handle and White score over 60% in those positions. Let's see how the game could continue after Black's three most common moves:} f5 {Not a simple move to make, but the best one according to the engine. Black closes the positions for our bishops and takes the [g4]-square under control.} 12. Rb1 {We can continue with our typcial ideas.} Qc7 13. O-O {[%cal Gf1c1]} Nge7 14. Rfc1 O-O 15. Bb4 {[%cal Gb4d6] We continue to increase the pressure and threaten to improve our bishop on [d6].} Qd7 16. Bb5 {[%csl Rc6,Rd7,Re7] With a complete paralysis. It is difficult for Black to find a move!} *

