with the pawn break ...[c5] and try to find counterplay on the queenside. White will try to build up an attack on the kingside thanks to their advanced [e5]-pawn.} c5 {Black immediately starts counterattacking the center.} 4. c3 {We reinforce our center.} Nc6 {The main move. Black continues their plan of putting pressure against White's center. All the other tries by Black on the fourth move will be explored in a specific chapter.} 5. Nf3 {We develop our knight on its natural square and give more protection to the [d4]-pawn. Now Black can try different moves. The first chapter of the course will examine the main move 5...[Qb6] and we will investigate all the other tries in the second one. The many transpositions from one move order to another will be explained throughout the course.} Nge7 {Black starts with the development of their knight first and wants to jump on [f5] to put pressure on our [d4]-pawn.} 6. Na3 $5 {Poisonous knight!} Nf5 7. Nc2 cxd4 8. cxd4 {And we are ready to continue with our typical ideas.} Qb6 {Black puts more pressure against the [d4]-pawn.} 9. Bd3 {We can continue our development as the [d4]-pawn is tactically protected.} Bd7 {Black develops the bishop and prevents all [Bb5]+ ideas after a capture on [d4].} 10. O-O {We complete our development and protect our king as the pawn is still tactically protected.} Be7 11. g4 {Black understands they can't take on [d4] and continue with their development. The drawback is that Black's knight can't retreat on [e7] from now on. This allows us to strike with our next move:} Nh4 {The natural continuation. But this doesn't work as after:} 12. Nxh4 Bxh4 13. g5 {The bishop is trapped!} h6 (13... h5 {Black prevents our queen to reach the h5-square. But we will still gain material after} 14. Qf3 {The queen is going to f4.} Nxd4 15. Qf4 Nxc2 16. Bxc2 {and Black will soon lose their dark-squared bishop.}) (13... O-O-O 14. Qg4 h6 15. Qxh4 hxg5 16. Qxg5 {Dynamics helped Black gain a tiny initiative, but their position remains objectively lost.}) 14. Qh5 {[%csl Rh8,Rh4] And Black will lose material on the next move.} *

